Key Match Events: Mitchell Strac dismissed Jonny Bairstow on the first ball of the 287-run chase
Joe Root walked to the crease to continue the chase
Adam Zampa clinched three wickets to derail England batting
Ben Stokes fought well scoring 64 runs
Australia defeated England by 33 runs to knock them out of the ICC World Cup 2023
Pre-Game Insights: Australia have made two forced changes in their playing XI with Marcus Stoinis and Cameron Green coming in for Mitchell Marsh and Glenn Maxwell
England have opted to go for the same side
Post-Match Reflections: Australia's victory against England in Ahmedabad officially knocked out defending champions out of the ICC World Cup 2023
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play, reducing the game to 20 overs per side
